[{"id":"VR615330","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"Two figures are shown. The first figure shows a student pushing a block to the right along a horizontal surface. The second figure shows a dot at the center of a 6 by 2 grid. There are 2 arrows extending from the dot. One arrow extends one unit to the left, and one arrow extends one unit to the right.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR615330.g06.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A student pushes a block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M sub 0\"><math alttext=\"M sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> over a rough horizontal surface at a constant velocity of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3 meters per second\"><math alttext=\"3 meters per second\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn><mtext> m/s</mtext></math></span></span> to the right, as shown in the figure. A free-body diagram of just the horizontal forces exerted on the block is also shown. A larger block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 M sub 0\"><math alttext=\"2 M sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> is then placed on top of the smaller block. The student again pushes the smaller block so that both blocks move together with the same constant velocity of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3 meters per second\"><math alttext=\"3 meters per second\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn><mtext> m/s</mtext></math></span></span> to the right. Which of the following free-body diagrams best represents the horizontal forces exerted on the bottom block in the second situation? The arrows representing the forces are all drawn to scale.</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR615330_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a dot at the center of a 6 by 2 grid. There are 2 arrows extending from the dot. One arrow extends one unit to the left, and one arrow extends one unit to the right.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR615330.g02.svg\"/></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a dot in a 6 by 2 gridded plane. Two arrows are extending from the dot. One arrow extends 3 units to the left, and one arrow extends 3 units to the right.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR615330.g03.svg\"/></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a dot at the center of a 6 by 2 grid. There are 3 arrows extending from the dot. One arrow extends one unit to the left, one arrow extends two units to the left, and one arrow extends three units to the right.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR615330.g04.svg\"/></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"inline_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a dot at the center of a 6 by 2 grid. There are 3 arrows extending from the dot. One arrow extends three units to the left, one arrow extends one unit to the right, and one arrow extends two units to the right.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR615330.g05.svg\"/></span></p>"],"answer":1}]